s-active-low-which-inverts-the-mental-model-of-signal-received-equals-pin-high","target":"ir-demodulator-output-is-active-low-which-inverts-the-mental-model-of-signal-received-equals-pin-high","line":34},{"title":"wiring-integration","target":"wiring-integration","line":37},{"title":"eda-fundamentals","target":"eda-fundamentals","line":38},{"title":"breadboard-intelligence","target":"breadboard-intelligence","line":39}],"metadata":{"description":"When a 74HC14 or similar inverting buffer is inserted between MCU and load for isolation, the firmware must invert every output command on those pins — what looks like digitalWrite(HIGH) produces LOW at the load, and forgetting the inversion makes the motor do the opposite of what was intended","type":"claim","source":"docs/parts/wiring-nodemcu-esp32-to-4x-zs-x11h-for-4wd-rover.md","confidence":"proven","topics":["[[wiring-integration]]","[[eda-fundamentals]]","[[breadboard-intelligence]]"],"related_components":[]},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[]},"smart_blocks:knowledge/signal-inversion-through-a-hex-inverting-buffer-requires-firmware-to-flip-every-driven-pins-logic-to-compensate.md#---frontmatter---": {"path":null,"last_embed":{"hash":"376f5h","at":1776157022988},"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[-0.08047497,-0.01075944,0.07569333,-0.03468133,-0.03563212,0.03184948,-0.02963043,0.02972057,0.00435484,0.00856219,0.03068334,-0.08546534,0.04088436,-0.01095234,0.06367451,0.00401756,-0.04079366,0.02890833,0.1030724,0.01608362,0.09262721,-0.03702496,-0.01174731,0.02069617,0.02491217,0.04750461,0.04601343,-0.05201437,-0.0493831,-0.25670075,-0.00046135,-0.02692828,0.01907674,-0.0185763,-0.01613057,-0.02411622,-0.03693395,-0.00818924,-0.03264653,0.07813005,0.01504552,-0.04880077,0.00485756,-0.06456874,0.0106229,-0.05343805,-0.04915285,-0.04585801,0.0369963,-0.05034697,-0.01507808,0.04668169,0.01697226,-0.04123268,0.04753542,0.02355176,0.06077525,0.09305594,0.00952525,-0.01766284,0.08020374,0.06195152,-0.